United Way of Fort Smith
September 2 at 1:06 PM ·

Due to Covid-19 we were not able to hold our traditional Fill the Bus School Supply Drive this year. We were able to go "virtual" and collect monetary donations. Because of the generosity of our donors we were able to present checks to 29 school districts in our six-county area. We would like to thank all of the companies and individuals that made this possible! Arkoma, Greenwood and Hackett also received checks but a picture was not available. #unitedwayfsa #fillthebus

August 13 at 10:38 AM ·

VIRTUAL SCHOOL ORIENTATION-
Monday , August 17 at 10:00 am the high school will be doing an orientation for all students (7th-12th) doing virtual classes. You will go to your classes so your teachers can give you needed information and materials. You will also pick up school supplies and your chromebooks. We will break out in small groups so social distancing will be possible. You will also need to wear your mask. It is important for you to be there at that time. Please respond so I know you received this email. We will start in the library. I can’t wait to see you.

post_text: County Line High School would like to welcome you and your parent(s)/guardian(s) to 7th grade Orientation on August 11, 2020 @ 6 pm. New students to CL are also welcome. There will be a meeting in the auditorium to discuss forms, schedules, and new rules at this time. It is important that you come to this meeting. 7th grade teachers will be there to introduce themselves. The high school will not be open and we will not be doing a campus tour but if your student would like one please call the office, set up a time and we will give a personalized tour. Please wear your mask and we will be practicing social distancing. We hope to see you there.

County Line FFA Chapter is with Amanda Price.
July 9 at 5:10 PM ·

With graduation scheduled for Sunday, we would like to recognize each of our 3 graduating senior officers this week. This evening we recognize our final senior officer, Madison Price! She has been an officer for the past 3 years, invested in countless volunteer hours, supported the chapter as one of our top fundraisers in Mum and Blue & Gold sales for several years, and been a member of the show team for 6 years and Food Science CDE team for 4 years, placing in the top 4 teams in state each of the past 3 years. She will be attending the University of Arkansas this fall to major in Agricultural Business.

post_text: Graduation will be held at 3:00 PM, Sunday July 12th in the auditorium. Due to COVID-19 safety guidelines admittance to the ceremony will be by ticket only (14 per graduate). Please write your name on the back of the ticket before entering the auditorium. The seating will be sectioned off by graduate. Family members of graduate must sit together (no exceptions). Masks and hand sanitizer will be made available. Thank you for your cooperation!

Due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, County Line High School will not be conducting athletic physicals for the 2020-2021 school year. If your child plans to participate in athletic activities (basketball, cheerleading, golf, softball, baseball or track) in the upcoming school year, they are required to have a physical. Parents will need to contact their primary care provider to schedule an appointment. Attached are the forms to be filled out by parent(s) and physician. Please return completed forms to the High School Office.

County Line Little League Baseball and Softball
May 3 at 1:41 PM ·

I’m posting this to look for some feedback. I am expecting it to be a June-July season at best. That allows for very very little if any practice time. It is also my concern that it is going to cut into time for 4H/FFA kids with their projects, as well as vacations and kids schedules who have to go out of town to mom/dads for summer. Ultimately the board will be voting on this, but what is everyone’s thoughts on cancelling this season? I know it’s not what anyone wanted but I’m concerned about the heat and safety of our kids, coaches, and umpires! Please let us know your thoughts!

County Line Little League Baseball and Softball
April 27 at 11:43 AM ·

The league has been talking about the tentative “reopen dates” throughout the state. If everything continues on track the way it is going, we will be playing our season in the months of June and July. If for whatever reason those dates are not going to work for your kiddo, please let us know. We have a lot of teams with very small numbers and 1 or 2 kids quitting could cause them to not have enough to play. We will not be issuing refunds of fees, however, we will roll them over to next years season if you choose for your child not to play this year. We will update more as soon as the governor releases official dates!

post_text:
County Line Cheer Tryouts will be held when we return to school in the fall.

In order to keep everyone safe and healthy, and to avoid conflicts with family. and other events this summer, we will have tryouts as soon as possible after we return to school.

Current junior high and senior high cheerleaders need to have their fees paid and uniforms returned as soon as possible before the end of school this year. Uniforms may be bagged and placed in the AMI box in front of the high school. Contact your coach about your fees.

Mrs. Brown and Ms. Looney want you to know that our first priority is for your health and safety.

Go Indians!

post_text:
Good Morning Parents and Guardians,
Every 10 years we are asked to do something very important that will affect the next 10 years of our children’s lives—count! The 2020 Census helps decide how much money your community will get for schools, child care and early learning, health insurance and medical care, early intervention and home visiting programs, food assistance, foster care, housing assistance, and public transport. Count all kids and babies at your address on the Census. Then, your local programs will get more funding to serve our children today and over the next decade.

It only takes 10 minutes, but it will impact the next 10 years.

Take the Census online, with multiple language options. Or you can call 844-330-2020 to complete the form by phone in English or find other by phone language options here.

Take the #2020Census! When you count all the children living at your address in the Census, programs in your community—like child care and food assistance—get more of the funding they need. Get more information at 2020Census.gov. #2020Census #CountAllKids #ARCounts

post_text: On Friday April 17th Camino our exchange student from Spain has to return home due to CO-VID 19 and schools closing. Please help us send her off by parking at the Caulksville Presbyterian at 10:00am this Friday. Shawna Stengel and her family will drive her through the parking lot so she can wave at you all one last time! They will be driving their white expedition. If you want, you could even make a sign and hold for her to read. With the social distancing we do have some rules. Please stay in your vehicles and park 6 ft from each other. Shawna did get approval from Brother Bill and Sheriff Massey. Thank you for helping Camino make memories this year!

Because of COVID-19’s impact on school closings, we are prepared to deliver your caps and gowns and class rings curbside. We are offering this in order for families to have their caps and gowns for pictures and family events, etc. Students will be able to pick up without having to enter the building. All orders will need to be paid in full. All payments will need to be made through Jostens.com or by calling 1-800-JOSTENS.

No checks or cash can be accepted on site - all social distancing guidelines and CDC rules to stay safe will be in effect.

Enter in by the auditorium and circle around to the high school on Friday, April 3rd from 9:00-11:00. Cars need to face south. We will be setting up under the awning between the high school and middle school. Please stay in your car - a Josten’s representative will assist you.

post_text:
County Line School District is accepting School Choice Applications for the 2020-2021 School Year.

The County Line School District will admit nonresident pupils to its school district under the Freedom of Choice Act pursuant to the provisions of Act 560, Public School Choice Act of 2015. The Arkansas Public School Choice program allows students to attend a school in which they do not reside subject to some restrictions. Applications must be filed in the nonresident district with a copy to the resident district or postmarked no later than May 1st of the year in which the student would begin the fall semester in the nonresident district. Applications may be mailed to 12092 State Highway 22 Branch, AR 72928 or dropped off at the school. If you have any questions regarding school choice feel free to call 479-635-2222. Application deadline is May 1, 2020.

post_text:
County Line Competes in FFA Mt. Magazine Subarea Leadership Events

On Wednesday, FFA members from ten schools in the river valley came together to compete at the Guy Fenter Education Service Cooperative in Branch for the Mt. Magazine Subarea Leadership Development Events. County Line FFA was represented by three members, Shae Parsons, Kaitlyn Vest, and Sunshine Xiong. Sunshine placed 5th in Creed Speaking. Kaitlyn placed 1st in Job Interview. And Shae placed 1st in the Farm Bureau Discussion Meet. Kaitlyn will advance to compete in the state Job Interview competition that will take place during the State FFA Convention in Hot Springs in April. Shae will advance to compete in the Northwest District competition that will also take place in Hot Springs in April. Congratulations to all three members!

post_text:
Congratulations BETA on a job well done! We are proud of all your hard work!

County Line BETA Club members won the following awards at the BETA State Convention in Hot Springs, AR this weekend: in Ag Science - 12th grader Shae Parsons took home 3rd place; 11th grader Kaitlyn Vest took home 2nd place; 10th grader Huntar Squires took home 1st. In Language Arts 10th grader Kirstyn Tyner took home 4th place. These students will be eligible to compete nationally at the BETA National Convention in June.
Congratulations to all our BETA members for their hard work and dedication to the principles of BETA Club.

The National Weather Service has issued a Winter Weather Advisory.

We are watching the weather closely, and because there is potential for icy roads we will be sending our AMI (Alternative Method of Instruction) materials home with elementary students this afternoon. AMI materials are available for secondary students online.

A decision about closing school will be made late tonight or early tomorrow morning if snow and ice make roads hazardous.

Please check the social and local media for up to date information.
